#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/disa_stig/disa_stig_part1.md:26
msgid ""
"In this guide we are going to cover how to apply the [DISA STIG for RHEL8]"
"(https://www.stigviewer.com/stig/red_hat_enterprise_linux_8/) for a New "
"Installation of Rocky Linux 8. As multi-part series, we will also be "
"covering how to test STIG compliance, adapt STIG settings, and apply other "
"STIG content in this environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/disa_stig/disa_stig_part1.md:28
msgid ""
"Rocky Linux is a bug for bug derivative of RHEL 8 and as such the content "
"published for the DISA RHEL8 STIG is in parity for both operating systems.  "
"Even better news, applying STIG settings is built into the Rocky Linux 8 "
"anaconda installer, under Security Profiles.  Under the hood this is all "
"powered by a tool called [OpenSCAP](https://www.open-scap.org/), which lets "
"you both configure the system to be compliant with the DISA STIG (fast!), "
"and also test the systems compliance after youâve installed."
